<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">6</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Nov 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1613</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1634</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18025507/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">18025507</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Nov 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.276065170">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=AIDS+%3D+acquired+immunodeficiency+syndrome&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">AIDS = acquired immunodeficiency syndrome</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FDG+%3D+fluorodeoxyglucose&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FDG = fluorodeoxyglucose</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=GIST+%3D+gastrointestinal+stromal+tumor&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">GIST = gastrointestinal stromal tumor</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=HIV+%3D+human+immunodeficiency+virus&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">HIV = human immunodeficiency virus</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MALT+%3D+mucosa-associated+lymphoid+tissue&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MALT = mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Lymphoproliferative disease of the solid organs and the gastrointestinal tract may affect any abdominopelvic tissue and may produce imaging features that resemble those of other diseases; nevertheless, an appropriate imaging strategy and a familiarity with disease-specific imaging features allow a provisional diagnosis as well as more accurate staging and more effective disease management.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Nuno Pinto</span> <span property="familyName">Leite</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology, Division of Body Imaging, University of California–San Diego, 200 W Arbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92103 (N.P.L., N.K., R.F.H., M.A.B., C.B.S.); and Department of Radiology, Hospital São João, Oporto Medical School, Miramar, Arcozelo, Portugal (N.P.L., J.M.P., R.C.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2004 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received September 18, 2006; revision requested October 4 and received February 21, 2007; accepted May 10. C.B.S. received research funding from Bayer and from GE Healthcare; all remaining authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="c